07/06/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The fight against unemployment is a priority for the Greek government, Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Friday (4 June) after meeting with new managers of the employment organisation OAED. 
He added that his cabinet would focus on youth unemployment and urged authorities to more efficiently utilise EU funds which could help curb the jobless rate and create new jobs.
In other news, Greek security chiefs start a tour of the Olympic cities on Monday, the last leg of preparations for the Games. 
Visits are planned to Volos, Thessaloniki, Heraklion and Patras, as well as to the regions bordering Turkey, Albania and Macedonia. 
(AP - 06/06/04; MPA - 04/06/04)
